textBeforeTable: marketing food brand management Arizona all employers See the complete Inventure Foods profile Inventure Foods - Inventure Foods is a Phoenix, AZ based snack food company that offers a “diverse lineup of innovative consumer brands sold both nationally and internationally.” Companies with Entry Level Jobs and Internships in Arizona As of 2012 the largest employers in Arizona are the government (including federal, state, and local), Wal-Mart, Banner Health, Wells Fargo, Bank of America, McDonalds, Raytheon, and JP Morgan. The state’s flagship institutions, the University of Arizona and Arizona State University, are also among their respective cities’ top employers. Much of the land in Arizona is government-owned, providing opportunities for those interested in the outdoors. Because of the abundance of preserved land and warm weather, tourism is also a big industry in Arizona. Located in the southwestern United States, Arizona is a state dominated by transportation, health care, and government industries. Its largest cities and economic hubs are Phoenix and Tucson.
